1. cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper is primarily focused on conversational agents and their natural language understanding, dialog management, and response generation capabilities. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the state-of-the-art techniques used by the university teams to build their socialbots, which falls under the domain of AI. 
3. cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper also discusses the engineering investments made by the Alexa Prize team to build and improve various components of the conversational AI system. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper mentions the Voice User Experience and tools for traffic management and scalability, which are important aspects of human-computer interaction. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper briefly touches upon the societal impact of conversational agents and their potential to solve real-world problems.
